<p>
					Welcome to the MIT Badminton club. </br><br /> 
The MIT Badminton club is <strong>only open to MIT affiliates (students, alum, faculty, staff, or spouse of any of the above)</strong>. These rules are set by the Club Sports Council at MIT and cannot be waived. For members of the general public who would like to play badminton at MIT, you may find the open recreational schedule on the MIT <a href="http://www.mitrecsports.com/">website</a>. These hours are updated weekly, and are <strong>not</strong> linked to the MIT Badminton Club in any way. <br /> <br /> 
For more information about joining, please click <a href="faqs.html">here</a>, and to view our club training schedule, please click <a href="https://web.mit.edu/mitbac/www/calendar/calendar.html">here</a> (MIT Certificate required).<br /> 
<br /> 

To contact us, you can email us at mitcbac-officers[at]mit[dot]edu. Please note that we cannot assist with open recreational badminton hours and these queries should be directly addressed to the MIT Z-Center staff.
					</p>
